OL,3,C'Someone who could do such a thing
OL,4,Cdoesn't deserve to live'
OL,6,F"When my mother and father came over,
OL,7,Fwe all went to school not speaking a
OL,8,Fword of English, but we all learned it.
OL,10,F"He was unique, his own man and had
OL,11,Fhis own way of doing things and he was
OL,12,Fan absolute foodie.
OL,14,F"Everybody loved him, he was jolly,
OL,15,Fcuddly, friendly, happy and that was
OL,16,Fhim."
OL,18,FRichard and his brother were
OL,19,Fincredibly close with Stuart visiting
OL,20,Fhim around five times a year.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/17
