OL,3,C'Someone who could do such a thing
OL,4,Cdoesn't deserve to live'
OL,6,F"Towards the end we just loved having
OL,7,Fthe close family there."
OL,9,FReflecting on the moment last year
OL,10,Fwhen he found out about his brother's
OL,11,Fdeath, he said: "Prior to the police
OL,12,Fcoming, I actually got a phone call
OL,13,Ffrom Greater Manchester Police who
OL,14,Fsaid to me 'we do believe that your
OL,15,Fbrother may be part of a murder
OL,16,Finvestigation and remains had been
OL,17,Ffound', or words to that effect.
OL,19,F"I said that can't be right because he
OL,20,Fonly sent me a birthday card the other
OL,21,Fday.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/17
