OL,3,C'Someone who could do such a thing
OL,4,Cdoesn't deserve to live'
OL,6,FIt was when two police liaison
OL,7,Fofficers came to Richard's house that
OL,8,Fhe "knew that Stuart was a victim of a
OL,9,Fmurder".
OL,11,F"They would not be contacting me, they
OL,12,Fwouldn't be offering liaison officers
OL,13,Funless they knew that that was my
OL,14,Fbrother.
OL,16,F"That was basically when it hit home
OL,17,Fand I could not believe it."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/17
