OL,3,C'Someone who could do such a thing
OL,4,Cdoesn't deserve to live'
OL,6,FRichard said that Stuart kept most of
OL,7,Ftheir parents possessions and
OL,8,Fheirlooms which were disposed of by
OL,9,FMajerkiewicz.
OL,11,F"All his possessions were thrown in
OL,12,Fthe bin (by Majerkiewicz) and that was
OL,13,Fthe history of the family, which hurts
OL,14,Fvery very badly."
OL,16,F"Once the reality of him being
OL,17,Fmurdered had come to light and then
OL,18,Fwhen I realised that the body parts
OL,19,Ffound in Kearsal dale were his, the
OL,20,Ffeeling I got was, 'how could anyone
OL,21,Fpossibly do anything like that'?
OL,26,@tD@IpmtD@Ypn
