OL,3,C'Someone who could do such a thing
OL,4,Cdoesn't deserve to live'
OL,6,FRichard said it was like "a dagger to
OL,7,Fthe heart", when he realised what had
OL,8,Fhappened to his brother.
OL,10,F"I was horrified thinking how anybody
OL,11,Fcould in the first instance murder my
OL,12,Fbrother, secondly dismembered him,
OL,13,Fthirdly, pretend to be him?
OL,15,F"All those things he did hurt equally
OL,16,Fbadly, all three things just
OL,17,Fculminated at just one horrendous time
OL,18,Fand to think what he must have gone
OL,19,Fthrough when he died is just
OL,20,Fremarkable."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/17
