OL,3,C'Someone who could do such a thing
OL,4,Cdoesn't deserve to live'
OL,6,F"The fact that (in court) he was
OL,7,Fdenying it and the defence, trying to
OL,8,Fput a case together on his behalf, was
OL,9,Fquite pathetic in my opinion because
OL,10,Fit was quite clear and obvious from
OL,11,Fday one that he was the murderer.
OL,13,F"He had a plan, not only to dismember
OL,14,Fmy brother but also to take his
OL,15,Fpossessions and money and he was
OL,16,Fplanning to disappear."
