OL,3,C'Someone who could do such a thing
OL,4,Cdoesn't deserve to live'
OL,6,F"When one human being takes another
OL,7,Fhuman being's life, there should be
OL,8,Fsome deterrent to prevent similar
OL,9,Fthings happening.
OL,11,F"I think some form of capital
OL,12,Fpunishment should be in place and he
OL,13,Fdoesn't deserve to be alive. Justice
OL,14,Fhas been done, but not quite."
OL,16,F"Someone who could do such a thing
OL,17,Fdoesn't deserve to live."
